cs 178 digital photography cs 178 digital photography spring 2009 what's inside a digital camera this is a cutaway view of the canon digital rebel 1000d here's a more instructive diagram showing the main optical paths we ll take apart a camera in class most photography books talk about depth of field and depth of focus but few of them give a formula for it here it is n is the f number f is focal length c is pixel size and u is distance to the scene we ll study this formula in class this is a tough shot because the arcade ceiling is much darker than the courtyard beyond i solved it by combining three exposures an idea called high dynamic range imaging you don t need a special camera for this we ll try it in class here are more shots from india dorothea lange's iconic portrait of a migrant mother during the great depression we ll survey the history of photography and we ll spend a lot of time taking pictures course materials click here for the 2010 version of the course with better lecture notes more applets etc course schedule click here for the lecture notes course description meeting time units prereqs etc course outline archive of class business the what's new from each day links to everyone's picasa web albums best photos for each of the weekly assignments assignment 1 bad photos due sunday april 5 11 59pm flash applet by andrew adams demonstrating that lenses perform a 3d perspective transformation flash applet demonstrating depth of field the dof at bottom means actual depth of field because the formula at top is only approximate assignment 2 sports & action due sunday april 12 11 59pm assignment 3 macro due sunday april 19 11 59pm eddy talvala's graphical summary of tradeoffs between camera settings flash applet demonstrating how a zoom lens can independently vary focal length and focusing distance assignment 4 architecture and interiors due sunday april 26 11 59pm slides summarizing what will be on the midterm revised 4 30 09 demonstration of quantization art